---
import workshopImage from "../assets/team/workshop.webp";
const importantDates = [
  { date: "May 25, 2026", event: "Paper Submission Deadline" },
  { date: "June 5, 2026", event: "Notification of Acceptance" },
  { date: "June 11, 2026", event: "Early Registration Deadline" },
  { date: "July 26, 2026", event: "Workshop Date" },
];
---

<section id="about" class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">

      <!-- Title -->
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 leading-tight mb-6 animate-on-scroll">
        Secure and Private System Design for Generative & Agentic AI
      </h2>

      <!-- Time & Location -->
      <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-1 animate-on-scroll">
        <span class="font-bold">Time:</span> 9:00 - 17:00 (PDT), July 26, 2026
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-8 animate-on-scroll">
        <span class="font-bold">Location:</span> Mtg Room 101A, Long Beach (Co-located with DAC 2026)
      </p>

      <!-- Image -->
      <div class="mb-10 animate-on-scroll">
        <img
          src={workshopImage.src}
          alt="Workshop Venue"
          class="w-1/2 max-w-sm mx-auto rounded-lg shadow-md object-cover"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Description -->
      <div class="text-left animate-on-scroll mb-12">
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed text-justify">
         Generative and agentic AI are reshaping computing at every layer, from research and infrastructure to the design of the systems themselves. As these capabilities are embedded into how silicon, software, and full-stack platforms get built and verified, both the threat surface and the means to defend it are being rewritten. The SPGAI 2026 Workshop on Secure and Private System Design for Generative and Agentic AI, co-hosted with the Design Automation Conference (DAC), confronts this dual frontier: hardening AI agents and the artifacts they generate against new and largely unmapped attack surfaces, while harnessing those same agents as a force multiplier for vulnerability discovery, secure-by-construction generation, automated compliance, and trustworthy verification. The program is organized around three intertwined themes — <strong>Secure, Private, and Trustworthy AI Agents, Securing the Artifacts of Agentic AI, and Generative and Agentic AI for Security, Privacy, and Trustworthiness</strong> — and welcomes contributions across EDA, chip and SoC security, quantum and neuromorphic computing, electro-optic co-design, and embedded and cyber-physical systems.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Important Dates -->
      <div class="text-left animate-on-scroll">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Important Dates:
        </h3>
        <div class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
          {importantDates.map((item) => (
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center py-3">
              <span class="text-gray-700">{item.event}</span>
              <span class="text-gray-800 font-medium ml-8 whitespace-nowrap">{item.date}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      <p class="mt-6 font-bold text-gray-900">
  More details available at <a href="#" onclick="showSection('topics'); return false;" class="text-primary-600 underline hover:text-primary-800">Call For Submissions</a>
</p>
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
